    <note>Xue(1) Jiqing [3388] It is interesting to note that Wang(2) Gui, in his funerary inscription for Jiqing, traces ancestry to the Sui dynasty official Daoheng [18767], rather than to Tang Gaozong's zaixiang, Xue(1) Yuanchao [18769], which would be the logical ancestor if one were fabricating a genealogy. Wang Gui, WJ, 59.1a-3a. The generational name of Jiqing matches that of the Southern Song, Hedong Xue, who lived in Yongjia as well as the Xue, who lived in Xinghua. CBD, 5, 4194.</note>
